Btw, I'm tired and won't proof-read this thing...so I'll apologize in advance<br>
for how choppy it is.<br>
<br>
Back in my day,  2 wizards could ks any group.  We were the masters of<br>
arcane magic.  Back then the only two classes with any complaints on<br>
balancing were warriors (In case you don't remember, warriors used to<br>
have nothing but berserker frenzy...which raised strength and attack a<br>
little) and Rouges (who had many..many broken skills).<br>
<br>
What I'm trying to say is, us wizards were just fine and dandy 'til Kunark<br>
came out.  All other classes shot way up to par with wizard abilities, like<br>
Druids and Mages, post 50, can nuke nearly as well as a wizard.  What the<br>
crap?<br>
<br>
The problem is, I believe, that there isn't a problem 'til post 50.  After<br>
level 50, groups stop needing wizards  They find ways around needing<br>
nukes and a quick evac.  In dungeons for post 50 levels, you really<br>
need to be a class that has a unique and much desirable skill to have this<br>
&quot;group utility&quot; (as the VI know-it-alls call it) in a group, correct?<br>
<br>
So VI (Verant Interactive) poops out some spells to &quot;enhance&quot; our class<br>
for &quot;group utility&quot;.<br>
<br>
-Translocates are excellent, but that has nothing to do with &quot;group utility&quot;.<br>
-Harvest is a very good try, and I'm sure it's useful at level 34 when it<br>
 first becomes available.<br>
-All the jokes hand ha ha's about Flickering Flame have been Exhausted...<br>
<br>
-Lastly, and the main focus of my post...the BANE spells and other level<br>
60 toys.<br>
<br>
VI has helped out the high level raid situation plenty.  All the useful<br>
enhancements have been put on the level 60 wizards (Sorcerers).<br>
However, they've done nothing for the before level 60.  It makes no<br>
sense at all.  We need help getting to level 60, not being level 60.<br>
<br>
I've given this new &quot;anti-mob Gate&quot; thing a thought, and asked others<br>
who aren't wizards how what they think of it.  Most give it a &quot;big whoop&quot;.<br>
All I've heard is that mob gating isn't really that big of a problem to<br>
inspire groups to go wizard hunting before entering a high level dungeon.<br>
<br>
Am I right or am I wrong? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 568<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 11:29 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do they keep enchancing Sorcerers?</span><hr size=1> Your logic is ok except for one point that fuels the REASON they won't help us.<br>
<br>
&quot;Back in my day, 2 wizards could KS an group.&quot;<br>
<br>
You're proud of that?  An ability that helps us break the rules?  That is where this entire mess started in the first place.  Of COURSE they changed it.<br>
<br>
But here is the real problem...<br>
Instead of JUST looking at that problem and making minor alterations to the class to avoid it, they developed a level of COMPLETE paranoya and cut off ALL talk of ANY damage development whatsoever.  Ok, they created more ports and transes.  Those have no direct impact on the KS'ing factor.<br>
<br>
<br>
KS'ing is what GOT us here.  So you mind as well say this entire excommunication of the wizard class is because a few of the choice wizards exploited our abilites, so they have cut us off all together.<br>
<br>
<br>
If the argument is our growth with the expansions, your logic is perfect.  But be careful of WHY you liked the old days.  If you liked the old days BECAUSE of KS'ing, then we DESERVE what we got.  There is more to it. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"><BR>59th Generation of Cazic - Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1871<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/01 11:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do they keep enchancing Sorcerers?</span><hr size=1> Well, the reason casters (NOT just Wizards, believe me) were able to kill steal was the way they credited kills.  It was the one person who got the most damage, not the group total damage.  When this was changed, the KS spectre (never a big problem in my experience playing back then) vanished. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=441.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=441.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=441.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topi